%% Reviewed 2026-04-17 for v0.1.11 to connect Tribunal dossier assembly and Remediator execution to Context Engine packets, Execution Engine snapshots, session memory, visible interventions, and benchmark proof.
sequenceDiagram
  participant Odylith as Odylith Observer
  participant Delivery as Delivery Intelligence
  participant Context as Context Engine
  participant Execution as Execution Engine
  participant Memory as Memory Substrate
  participant Dossier as Dossier Builder
  participant Actors as Tribunal Actors
  participant Judge as Adjudicator
  participant Editor as Editor
  participant Remediator as Remediator
  participant Visibility as Visible Intervention Broker
  participant Benchmark as Benchmark Harness
  participant Approval as Approval Ledger
  participant Operator as Maintainer
  participant Clearance as Clearance Check
  participant Runtime as Runtime v4 Store

  Odylith->>Delivery: Select changed or contested scope
  Delivery->>Context: Request compact packet digest
  Context-->>Dossier: Packet quality, target resolution, route readiness
  Delivery->>Execution: Request compact execution snapshot
  Execution-->>Dossier: Admissibility, next move, validation, closure
  Delivery->>Memory: Request session and delivery-ledger summary
  Memory-->>Dossier: Recent corrections, proof events, visible delivery state
  Delivery->>Dossier: Assemble case dossier with repo objects, checkpoints, approvals, and evidence
  Dossier->>Actors: Run observer, ownership, causal, policy, normative, adversary, counterfactual, gap, risk, prescriber
  Actors-->>Judge: Actor memos + disagreement
  Judge->>Judge: Choose leading explanation, rival explanation, and confidence
  Judge->>Editor: Produce decision brief + systemic context
  Judge->>Remediator: Hand off executable prescription candidate
  Editor->>Visibility: Emit compact intervention signal when user-visible risk is earned

  alt No bounded execution path
    Remediator-->>Odylith: Manual-only recommendation
    Odylith->>Runtime: Persist outcome without packet
  else Bounded packet candidate
    Remediator->>Remediator: Compile deterministic, AI-engine, or hybrid packet
    Remediator->>Approval: Persist fingerprint, preconditions, validation, rollback
    Odylith->>Runtime: Persist case, reasoning, posture, and packet state
    Operator->>Odylith: Approve or reject packet
    alt Deterministic packet approved
      Odylith->>Remediator: Execute bounded local action
      Remediator->>Clearance: Run validation + stale checks
    else AI-engine or hybrid packet approved
      Remediator-->>Operator: Emit constrained AI-engine handoff
      Operator->>Odylith: Record outcome after external execution
      Odylith->>Clearance: Run post-action validation
    else Rejected or stale
      Approval-->>Odylith: Keep case contested or reopen
    end
    Clearance-->>Odylith: Cleared, failed, or reopened
    Clearance->>Benchmark: Record closure, validation, false-admit or false-deny evidence
    Odylith->>Runtime: Update posture and clearance state
  end
